# Code owners — require an explicit HUMAN review on every PR.
#
# Why: branch protection requires a code-owner approval to merge. A bot reviewer
# (e.g. CodeRabbit) is NOT a code owner, so its approval can never satisfy the gate
# — only a real owner's can. This closes the "a bot rubber-stamps the merge" hole.
#
# Solo-repo note: GitHub forbids approving your own PR, so the maintainer merges
# their own PRs via admin override (`gh pr merge --admin`) — a conscious bypass,
# never a silent one. External contributors' PRs are fully gated.

